Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.76,0:02:01.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Working as hard as ever, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.09,0:02:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.99,0:02:06.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going over to a newspaper company.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.92,0:02:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They seem to got interested in my work in ESP and wants to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.79,0:02:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good for you. Hope it works out for you, not like the last time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.68,0:02:24.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like my works are going to be published in very near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.04,0:02:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My project is also approaching completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.43,0:02:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's bitter and sweet work.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.84,0:02:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to give it a try?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.68,0:02:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One sip and you'll be in dreamy paradise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.22,0:02:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only if you're willing to exchange your life for that though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.54,0:02:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange for my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.02,0:03:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, don't be reserved.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.99,0:03:06.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not reserving myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.91,0:03:07.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.94,0:03:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,NOOOO!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.69,0:03:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.96,0:03:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perfect. Guys, coffee is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.31,0:03:47.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.47,0:03:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're late, Noda-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.54,0:03:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.62,0:03:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you wear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.11,0:03:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.05,0:04:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's mean! Remember, you promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.15,0:04:07.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But.. it's too embarrassing, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.65,0:04:16.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could you? It was my dream..  It's my dream to date.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.13,0:04:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it was your dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.29,0:04:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We bought in pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.50,0:04:26.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if we run into our friends, they might take it in wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.74,0:04:33.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.71,0:04:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.11,0:04:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forgot. I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.02,0:04:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's talk about this later, and why don't we grab something to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.14,0:05:00.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say? This's my research essay on twin ESPers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.68,0:05:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- This paper would astonish the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.55,0:05:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.64,0:05:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me. I've got an unexpected guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait till you see this! With this paper, your paper will double the sales.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.88,0:05:26.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our local section reporter is itching to hear your story.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.34,0:05:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show you the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.91,0:05:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.76,0:05:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the local section.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.34,0:05:38.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very grateful for your help.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.76,0:05:40.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.45,0:05:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.44,0:05:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, this's the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.58,0:06:02.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Would you try another paper?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.74,0:06:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.55,0:06:12.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good bye.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.41,0:06:27.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.38,0:06:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you knock it off?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.78,0:06:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The editor is in a meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.39,0:06:55.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, will you leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.18,0:06:56.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This's a big scoop!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.17,0:07:11.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My essay! {maybe better "My papers?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.88,0:07:40.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? A whirlwind?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.05,0:07:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go! My history making essay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.94,0:08:08.98,announce,,0000,0000,0000,,Large and powerful Typhoon #3 will head north and hit Honshu by tomorrow evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.17,0:08:12.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe this. It's still May.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.90,0:08:18.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.47,0:08:27.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.62,0:08:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Something happened with Noda?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.35,0:08:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Can you tell me what Noda-kun and I are?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.68,0:08:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What made you say that?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.62,0:08:44.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I never really checked how he felt about me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.14,0:08:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's a bit dull, but I'm sure he knows how you feel about him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.34,0:08:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to be sure about his feeling to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.87,0:09:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally occurring radioactive isotopes are classified into three groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.30,0:09:45.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Be" verb plus present particle, that is, "ing" added to the root.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.11,0:09:48.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For instance, "Tom is looking out of the window."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.00,0:09:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.36,0:09:53.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.30,0:09:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mid term is coming up soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.49,0:10:00.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pay attention or you'll get a "F" mark again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.94,0:10:03.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You hit me with the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.82,0:10:15.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Destroy everything and create something anew.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.01,0:10:19.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Destroy everything and create something anew.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.98,0:10:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Matsunaga-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.92,0:10:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Younger Matsunaga?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:30.99,announce,,0000,0000,0000,,Due to the approaching of typhoon, the afternoon classes are canceled.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.22,0:11:35.67,announce,,0000,0000,0000,,All students, please go home immediately. I repeat...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.76,0:11:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.08,0:11:41.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Better. And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.31,0:11:45.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine. But I wonder why both of us collapsed at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.65,0:11:49.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like nobody else heard the noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.15,0:11:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.32,0:11:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.29,0:11:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our telepathy linked, and synced with something.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.71,0:12:03.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard that sharp sound in ears, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.24,0:12:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And had a shock like electricity ran through my body.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.94,0:12:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My ears are still ringing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.57,0:12:10.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.99,0:12:13.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's one down side of telepathy, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.93,0:12:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.81,0:12:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oops, noticed me? Bummer, I wanted to surprise you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.41,0:12:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted to peep, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.86,0:12:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that all you got to say when I dropped by worried about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.77,0:12:28.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What worry?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.31,0:12:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You just wanted to scared us and see if we pass out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.26,0:12:39.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi, I gotta pick up something, so go ahead and go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.77,0:12:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, the bugger can go home alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.40,0:12:54.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Younger Matsunaga.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.65,0:13:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard all your conversation in the medical room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.07,0:13:07.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to know more about the telepathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.63,0:13:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Date?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.33,0:13:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting at the same spot as yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.50,0:13:18.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But looks at the weather.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.37,0:13:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think date in a typhoon is gonna be fun?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.97,0:13:25.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, promise me you'll come.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.41,0:13:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Promise?... Wait, Tomomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.24,0:13:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why today, not tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.05,0:13:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, stop Tomomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.64,0:13:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.99,0:13:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.53,0:13:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, if you really want to know, I can show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.01,0:13:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me this is a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.37,0:13:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't you hold me responsible for whatever could happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.86,0:13:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why should I? There's no way!!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.16,0:13:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.08,0:14:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave it up to your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.58,0:14:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you quit laughing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.54,0:14:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\q2\fsp-0.5}I mean, Kageura was scared as hell, \Nthinking even the thunder was because of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.70,0:14:22.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's too funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.43,0:14:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not funny at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.18,0:14:26.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you tell Kageura?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.47,0:14:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.33,0:14:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just suddenly felt like making fun of Kageura.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.07,0:14:43.03,announce,,0000,0000,0000,,Large and powerful Typhoon #3 has picked up strength, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:46.09,announce,,0000,0000,0000,,will land in Honshu by the evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.33,0:14:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.11,0:14:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I felt I should big papers like your's should know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.57,0:14:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, this is an event of the century.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.18,0:15:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're serious about showing ESP to Kageura-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.11,0:15:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.43,0:15:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him I'll show it today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.07,0:15:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But imagine what kind of trouble we could be in!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.56,0:15:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on. It'll make us feel easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.65,0:15:15.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't be ordinary high school students anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.56,0:15:18.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Kurashige-sempai and Noda already know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.85,0:15:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they're exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.61,0:15:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember we promised to keep it secret to even dad or mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.67,0:15:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare they take me so lightly!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.95,0:15:35.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin-chan, lunch is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.09,0:15:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for food. {scary food those guys have... probably he waste so much money for voodoo stuff... Poor Rika!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.79,0:15:41.11,announce,,0000,0000,0000,,Who could do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.59,0:15:45.56,announce,,0000,0000,0000,,We found a penguin with an arrow piercing its body in Inokashira Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Delicious, Rika-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.60,0:15:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good. I'm glad I got the ingredients from Papua New Guinea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.69,0:15:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{arg... missing subtitle... I would assume he speaks about a alien of some sorts}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.86,0:15:55.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shin-chan, watch your manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.64,0:16:00.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{probably something like How mysterious... How frightening... hate missing lines}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.69,0:16:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, is there anybody in the audiences who experienced strange things like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.87,0:16:08.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Call us right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.04,0:16:12.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our blitz reporter will get to you very quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.10,0:16:13.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.42,0:16:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired of hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.72,0:16:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to tell everything and get it over with.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.81,0:16:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.19,0:16:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.96,0:16:34.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At last! The moment I have been waiting for is here!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.29,0:17:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The day has finally come for me to be the big name in science world!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.97,0:17:10.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Date with Noda?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.44,0:17:11.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.64,0:17:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's a typhoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.27,0:17:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you change to another day?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.84,0:17:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't. We already promised.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.26,0:17:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get this feeling that I can find out Noda-kun's feeling to me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.43,0:17:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Tomomi...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.63,0:17:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to get rid of this uncertainty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.56,0:17:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't acting like yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.26,0:17:36.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Neither you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.98,0:17:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of all other days, why today?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.68,0:17:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if it's OK with her if the sweat shit get all wet.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.08,0:17:49.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's she up to?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:56.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you certain, we'll get to see the greatest twin ESPer of the century?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.41,0:17:59.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. Why else would I call you people?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.19,0:18:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But why do you have to carry out the experiment in the middle of typhoon?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.13,0:18:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you see? The strange power within typhoon enhance the strength of ESP.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.06,0:18:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be sure to film it properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.43,0:18:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's going to be the biggest event of the century.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.88,0:18:18.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.43,0:18:23.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll teleport you so that you can make it to the date, so will you come with me first?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.22,0:18:25.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.18,0:18:26.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.99,0:18:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pushy girl you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.05,0:18:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.00,0:18:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,End it in three minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.55,0:18:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.50,0:18:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Younger Matsunaga, glad you kept your promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.20,0:18:48.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to startle you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.87,0:18:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to see you two in this storm with just lights of the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.93,0:18:54.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.73,0:18:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now can you begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.95,0:19:01.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the middle of this storm, it'll begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.54,0:19:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're just about to see the history in making.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.44,0:19:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She told me to come and she's late.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.45,0:19:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.96,0:19:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A tornado?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.09,0:20:01.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi, are you OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.04,0:20:03.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mikage!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.65,0:20:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.43,0:20:09.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noda-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.15,0:20:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noda-kun, I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.05,0:20:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't embarrass me..
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.93,0:20:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Congrats, Tomomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.68,0:20:40.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You only had the tornado on the video?! Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.08,0:20:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare they call me boaster!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.25,0:20:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.03,0:20:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.34,0:21:01.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikage, it feels so good doing this!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.44,0:21:04.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did we do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.35,0:21:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.02,0:21:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.38,0:21:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning. Thank you about yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.41,0:21:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mention it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.58,0:21:17.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't remember about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.26,0:21:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did I say something when you came to save me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.10,0:21:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing I can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.11,0:21:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.82,0:21:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miracle Girls here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.80,0:21:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's lost in hiking.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.10,0:21:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There're bears around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.17,0:21:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. Noda-kun's with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.83,0:21:57.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? With him?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.08,0:22:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next on Miracle Girls:\N"Bearing to South South West"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.37,0:22:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to be lost with Noda?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.88,0:22:08.30,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.43,0:22:11.60,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,there has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.51,0:22:14.93,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we had a fight,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.18,0:22:18.15,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,There has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.03,0:22:34.79,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,There are days when kindness is so close
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.04,0:22:38.08,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,, that you can't see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.37,0:22:51.60,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we know it better than anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.14,0:22:58.02,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,When we can't say "I'm sorry,"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.10,0:23:05.07,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,we send out feelings through the little fingers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.82,0:23:11.82,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Going over the tears,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.16,0:23:14.74,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,we want to be honest to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.04,0:23:20.17,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,'Cause the sky deserves a rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.92,0:23:23.21,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever we do,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.42,0:23:26.67,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,there has to be both of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.55,0:23:29.76,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,Two of us
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.93,0:23:33.14,song-ed,,0000,0000,0000,,are better than one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.15,0:22:24.65,credits,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Ending Song\N"There has to be Both of Us"\N("Futarijanakya Dame Nano")\NBy Dio
